{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Encourage banks not to refuse mortgages for properties with high service charge",
        "additional_details": "With increasing compliance and fire inspection costs, utilities and contractor fees, it has caused some service charges to rise to more than 1% of the value of the apartment.\r\n\r\nGiven that banks have been bailed out by taxpayers multiple times, we think it is time for the government to support trapped sellers in return.\r\n",
        "background": "There have been reports that some banks are not providing mortgages on some properties with high service charges. I urge the government to intervene.",
